				<td colspan="2"><span>You can also Charm kite giants, woolly mamoths, rinos in the south part of Easternwastes. Grab the ulthork man o wars for the tusks to turn in to othmers if you feel like it. Back when BD were rare this was a good money/xp area
<br />

<br />
If you wanna practice swarm kiting you should start with light blues. Or a zone where you know they will turn light blue your next level. At 40 Wallies in EW are A pretty decent bet. Use the ulthorks as pet. They will give you better Damage and wont drop to fast. the wallies run speed is base so you won't need to use selos all the time. (if you can pick up t or j boots.) Start off with about 5 mobs. Make sure you rember to bring your wind instrument. invisable to break charm when your pet is low on health then chant kite it down. Snag a nother pet and repeat.  Giants run fast and have a long reach so there not the best to practice on. 
<br />

<br />
Rao</span></td>
