				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Level 40 new to bards <a name="73179"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 13 05 10:46 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>OK first I wanna stir this pot... then I'll answer the question.
<br />

<br />
40 and new to bards...ugh!!!  However you got there you have shortchanged yourself as a bard.  If you WANT to you can recover from that, but it will take some work.
<br />

<br />
As to chant kiting not being &quot;kiting in the typical sense&quot; ..uumm... what do you think kiting IS?  First I ever hear of kiting was druids and shaman casting a dot on a mob and running away from it around the zone.  The mob was like a kite on a string following at a distance and slowly dying.  This is EXACTLY what chant-kiting is.
<br />

<br />
The MOST important aspect of ANY casting class is knowing what your spells/songs DO.  You just GOTTA know the song lineup. If in fact you do know the song line-up at 40 you know we have the following songs which are single target, percussion based, damage over time songs.
<br />

<br />
30 - Fufil's Curtailing Chant
<br />
38 - Tuyen's Chant of Flame
<br />
42 - Tuyen's Chant of Disease
<br />
46 - Tuyen's Chant of Frost
<br />
50 - Tuyen's Chant of Poison
<br />

<br />
There are more that replace these in the 60s.  These songs stack with each other because they are 5 different resist checks.
<br />

<br />
So at 40 you can twist 2 chants.. fufils and flame... I would throw in a bruscoe's boastful bellow in the gap to add some damage... at 42 you can up your damage output by adding Chant of Disease and so on.  Keep running away, either with selos or sow and tisisting the songs.. and eventually the mob dies.
<br />

<br />
Chant kiting can take a looonnnng time taking a mob from full to dead, but there is no downtime between, the bard takes no damage.
<br />

<br />
Now to swarming... due to the tone of Muskratt's original post, I have a feeling we need to DEFINE swarming here, just to be sure he isnt thinking AOE kiting.  They are NOT the same thing.
<br />

<br />
Swarm kiting involves social mobs.. that is mobs that will assist one another when attacked.  
<br />
You charm one mob.. 
<br />
Send it in to a pack of social mobs 
<br />
They tear your new charmed pet to little bits for attacking one of them
<br />
You break charm before your pet dies
<br />
You chant kite the last ...oh... 10 percent or so of your ex-pet and get full XPS
<br />
You charm another mob in the swarm and repeat the process
<br />

<br />
Your melee skills suffer greatly if you do this exclusively, but noone can PL you this fast.
<br />

<br />
Now if Muskratt learns to kite from this I feel I may have done you a dis-service.  You need to group.. melee.. buff.. debuff.. learn to be a bard and develop bard skills both for the toon and the player.  You are already behind on that curve, swarming will put you further behind if you do just it.  My melee skills suffered because I leveled so fast in that range, but they were ok at the start and I was motivated to bring them up.  I love being a bard.
<br />

<br />
Best of Luck,
<br />
Reys
<br />

<br />

<br />
</span></td>
